-- China's Exim  Bank Lends Mozambique $65 Million for Airport, Pais Reports
-- Fred Katerere
-- 2010-06-22T05:43:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/china-s-exim-bank-lends-mozambique-65-million-for-airport-pais-reports.html

          
          
             Export-Import Bank of China will
lend Mozambique $65 million to build the domestic terminal of
the southern African country’s international airport in the
capital, Maputo, o Pais reported today.  
 The lender, which also financed improvements of the
international terminal, will provide funds for the construction
of four rural schools, an agricultural college and 150 houses in
the capital, according to the Maputo-based newspaper. It didn’t
say how much those projects would cost.  
